column1: LUT for the Sunglint Pointing Enhancement (Goyens and Ruddick
rho_u = pi*L(surface reflected)/Ed (dimensionless) at theta_v as in Goyens and Ruddick
vza1 and vza2 are viewing zenith angle from 20 to 80° as in Goyens and Ruddick
w stands for wind speed in m/s ranging from 1 to 14 m/s
D is the D factor as in Goyens and Ruddick
SZA is the solar zenith angle ranging from 20 to 70°
amod is aerosol model accordinf to Shettle and Fenn (1979)
